<h1 itemprop="headline name">Why Do White Supremacists Love Tucker Carlson So Much?</h1>
<span class="byline"><span itemprop="author" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><a href="https://forward.com/author/aiden-pink/" itemprop="url" class="author-name"><span itemprop="name">Aiden Pink</span></a></span><span><span class="date" itemprop="datePublished">March 17, 2019</span><meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2019-03-17T05:00:00-04:00"></span><span class="photo-credit"><a href="https://forward.com/artist/phillip-faraone-getty-images-for-politicon/">Phillip Faraone/Getty Ima...
						</a></span></span><meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2019-03-17T05:00:00-04:00">
</div></div></header>
</div>
<div class="container article-columns-container resizing-columns"><div class="row">
<div class="col-14 offset-1 article-content-column">
<div class="photo-credit-mobile"><a href="https://forward.com/artist/phillip-faraone-getty-images-for-politicon/">Phillip Faraone/Getty Ima...
						</a></div>
<ul class="social-nav mobile nocontent">
<li><a href="#" class="js-recommend-article"><em class="social icon email"></em><span>Email</span></a></li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?app_id=113869198637480&amp;u=https://forward.com/news/national/420970/why-do-white-supremacists-love-tucker-carlson-so-much/&amp;display=popup&amp;ref=plugin" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?app_id=113869198637480&amp;u=https://forward.com/news/national/420970/why-do-white-supremacists-love-tucker-carlson-so-much/&amp;display=popup&amp;ref=plugin"><em class="social icon facebook"></em><span>Facebook</span></a></li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Why%20Do%20White%20Supremacists%20Love%20Tucker%20Carlson%20So%20Much%3F&amp;url=http://jd.fo/XBnW&amp;via=jdforward&amp;source=webclient" data-href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Why%20Do%20White%20Supremacists%20Love%20Tucker%20Carlson%20So%20Much%3F&amp;url=http://jd.fo/XBnW&amp;via=jdforward&amp;source=webclient"><em class="social icon twitter"></em><span>Twitter</span></a></li>
</ul>
<div itemprop="articleBody" class="article-content dropcaps">
<p>Here’s what white supremacists said about Fox News Channel host Tucker Carlson when they thought no one else was looking:</p>
<p>“Tucker is really doing divine work.”</p>
<p>“A lone voice of reason in the media.”</p>
<p>“Tucker is a blessing, def[initely] our guy.”</p>
<p>The uproar this past week over numerous recently-uncovered insensitive comments Carlson made on a radio show overshadowed news that could have been even worse for him: A <a href="https://unicornriot.ninja/2019/neo-nazi-hipsters-identity-evropa-exposed-in-discord-chat-leak/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">massive leak of internal chat logs</a> from Identity Evropa, one of the leading white supremacist groups in America, showed that many members were huge fans of Carlson and the ideas he espoused every night to millions of viewers.</p>
<div class="container ad-unit native-ad-unit" data-zone="136" id="native-ad" data-type="dynamic" data-pid="0" data-alias="/"></div>
<div id="forward-video-ad-6" class="forward-video-ad"></div>
<p>Even though white supremacist groups themselves have <a href="https://forward.com/news/national/418155/white-supremacist-daily-stormer-andrew-anglin/">largely gone underground</a> – either due to financial pressures, fear of their identities being revealed or infighting – they have continued to try to push their ideologies into the mainstream. And they see Carlson as a key component in that effort.</p>
<p>“Tucker Carlson has long been praised by white nationalists as being one of them or supporting their talking points,” Spencer Sunshine, an associate fellow at the think tank Political Research Associates who studies far-right movements, told the Forward.</p>
<p>Fox News did not respond to a request for comment.</p>
<p>In December 2018, one user <a href="https://cloudfront.mediamatters.org/static/uploader/image/2019/03/07/Screen_Shot_2019-03-07_at_12.51.35_PM.png" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">described</a> a “Twitter food chain” where information passes from white supremacist podcasts and YouTube shows, to Rep. Steve King and commentator Ann Coulter, to Carlson, to President Trump. A similar comment was <a href="https://cloudfront.mediamatters.org/static/uploader/image/2019/03/07/Screen_Shot_2019-03-07_at_1.18.20_PM.png" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">made</a> two months later: “Tucker is basically the only funnel from the base to [Trump] at this point.”</p>
<div class="row"></div>
<h3 style="display:none" itemprop="headline name" data-headline=""></h3>
<aside class="article-listing article-related has-more-related"><article><meta content="https://forward.com/news/national/420970/why-do-white-supremacists-love-tucker-carlson-so-much/">
<figure class="col-5"><div class="share-cta"><a href="https://forward.com/news/national/418155/white-supremacist-daily-stormer-andrew-anglin/" data-attribution-id="articles-article-related-1-img"><img data-src="https://images.forwardcdn.com/image/303x227/center/images/cropped/richardspencerwhitesupremacist-1548778030.jpg" data-high-res="https://images.forwardcdn.com/image/303x227/center/images/cropped/richardspencerwhitesupremacist-1548778030.jpg" alt="Why Do White Supremacists Love Tucker Carlson So Much? by the Forward" title="Why Do White Supremacists Love Tucker Carlson So Much?" class=" " width="303" height="227"><meta itemprop="representativeOfPage" content="true">
<meta itemprop="url" content="https://images.forwardcdn.com/image/303x227/center/images/cropped/richardspencerwhitesupremacist-1548778030.jpg">
<meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://images.forwardcdn.com/image/303x227/center/images/cropped/richardspencerwhitesupremacist-1548778030.jpg">
<meta itemprop="author" content="Nikki Casey">
<meta itemprop="width" content="2280">
<meta itemprop="height" content="1460">
