<li><a target="_blank" class="social icon twitter" href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=ADL%20Condemns%20Trump%20For%20Tweeting%20South%20Africa%20White%20Nationalist%20Conspir&amp;url=https://forward.com/fast-forward/408782/adl-condemns-trump-for-tweeting-south-africa-white-nationalist-conspiracy/&amp;via=jdforward&amp;source=webclient">Twitter</a></li>
<li><a target="_blank" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https://forward.com/fast-forward/408782/adl-condemns-trump-for-tweeting-south-africa-white-nationalist-conspiracy/&amp;media=https://images.forwardcdn.com/image/center/images/cropped/gettyimages-831377106-1502829697.jpg" class="social icon pinterest">Pinterest</a></li>
<li><a href="#" class="social icon email js-recommend-article" data-article="408782" data-headline="ADL Condemns Trump For Tweeting South Africa White Nationalist Conspiracy Theory" data-link="https://forward.com/fast-forward/408782/adl-condemns-trump-for-tweeting-south-africa-white-nationalist-conspiracy/">Email</a></li>
</ul></nav></div></a></div></figure><div class="col-18 push-1">
<p class="rel-item"><a href="https://forward.com/fast-forward/408782/adl-condemns-trump-for-tweeting-south-africa-white-nationalist-conspiracy/" data-attribution-id="articles-article-related-1-headline">ADL Condemns Trump For Tweeting South Africa White Nationalist Conspiracy Theory</a></p>
<span class="byline" data-attribution-id="articles-article-related-1-byline"><span itemprop="author" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><a href="https://forward.com/author/jta/" itemprop="url" class="author-name"><span itemprop="name">JTA</span></a></span><span><span class="date" itemprop="datePublished">August 23, 2018</span><meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-08-23T14:00:00-04:00"></span></span>
</div></article></aside><p>And he also alludes to the perceived inferiority of non-white people. Last December, for example, he claimed immigrants made the United States “dirtier,” which led at least <a href="https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/advertisers-tucker-carlson-fox-news-1203093497/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">30 companies to say they wouldn’t air ads on his show anymore.</a> More have left since the Media Matters investigation dropped.</p>
<p>To be sure, Carlson has <a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/erik-wemple/wp/2017/11/29/i-cant-reveal-my-confidential-sources-mr-wemple-the-tucker-carlson-interview/?utm_term=.aa243371375a" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">frequently denied</a> that he <a href="https://www.cjr.org/the_profile/tucker-carlson.php" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">uses his platform</a> to <a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/erik-wemple/wp/2018/11/29/tucker-carlson-neo-nazi-favorite/?noredirect=on&amp;utm_term=.5f36df19cba7" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">disseminate and sanitize white nationalism.</a> But many media critics – and perhaps most saliently, white nationalists themselves - continue to think he’s doing so.</p>
<p>Sunshine cautioned against trying to read Carlson’s mind for proof of his ideological intentions. “We don’t know if he’s intentionally, self-consciously thinking like a white nationalist and soft-selling it,” he said. “But I think we can see empirically that…what he’s saying harmonizes with white nationalist views. And we can see that when <em>they</em> say it [does].”</p>
<p>Indeed, a <a href="https://www.mediamatters.org/blog/2019/03/08/leaked-chat-messages-show-members-white-supremacist-group-identity-evropa-are-obsessed-tucker/223083" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Media Matters analysis</a> of the Identity Evropa leaks revealed widespread adulation for Carlson.</p>
<p>Carlson has also been praised on the white supremacist website <a href="https://dailystormer.name/new-batch-of-tucker-comments-is-even-better-white-people-created-civilization/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">The Daily Stormer</a> and podcasts like <a href="https://www.mediamatters.org/research/2018/11/20/tucker-carlson-hero-these-white-supremacist-podcasts/222124" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">The Daily Shoah.</a> Former Ku Klux Klan leader David Duke declared last year that Carlson is one of “the voices we have in the media on our side.”</p>
<p>Ultimately, the extent to which Carlson continues to promote dialogue that white nationalists approve of will be governed by whether the experience chastises him – or whether the advertiser exodus forces Fox to take tighter control. So far, things appear to be continuing largely as before.</p>
<p>Carlson was defiant on his shows this week. He said he was being targeted by a “liberal mob.”</p>
<p>“These are the people who write our movies and our sitcoms,” he said on Monday. “They are not shocked by naughty words. They just pretend to be when it’s useful. It’s been very useful lately.”</p>
<p>The reference to Hollywood cultural elites was <a href="https://forward.com/fast-forward/420795/tucker-carlson-anti-semitic-fox-news/">interpreted by some</a> as a veiled reference to Jews.</p>
